       Just before she was sent into reality, Aracnia saw a bright flash of 
numbers sprawl across a vast landscape. Then, it was replaced by the face of 
Quickstrike, a concerned look on his face.
       "Are you alright? Is our child alright? Where, where is our child?" 
She said, still holding onto Quickstrike in a weak state. She turned her head 
to the strange bot on the bunk. "Is that our...daughter?"

--part1_4f.422ecaa.2756c47e_boundary
